definitions.definition: to move (something) from one place to another.
examples: We had to relocate the magazine rack because we bruised our shins on it too frequently when it was near the door.

definitions.definition: to change one's domicile or place of business .
examples: Alfred relocated to Colorado Springs to take advantage of the boom in the defense industry.

definitions.definition: to lose something and find it again .
examples: I relocated the bird I spotted last week.

main_definition: ( transitive ) to move (something) from one place to another.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) to change one's domicile or place of business .
( intransitive ) to lose something and find it again .
